, 
<figureCitation box="[256,293,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1781,1803]" captionTargetBox="[174,1411,618,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,585,1719]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. Dorsal habitus. a. A. adaucta Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; b. A. akazu (Matsumura, 1932); c. A. badjawae Dworakowska, 1976; d. A. bauhinicola Dworakowska &amp; Viraktamath, 1978; e. A. curva Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; f. A. expansa Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; g. A. falcata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; h. A. fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; i. A. jinghongensis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; j. A. liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; k. A. maculosa Dworakowska, 1977; l. A. parisakazu Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; m. A. plana Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; n. A. qinlingensis Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; o. A. quadrata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; p. A. sphenoides Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; q. A. subapicifixa Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; r. A. subdentata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; s. A. sufflata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; t. A. symmetrica Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; u. A. triangulata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; v. A. triprocessa Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; w. A. wolongensis Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; x. A. zelta Dworakowska, 1977." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444150/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">25j</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,258,535]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Crown yellowish, with two beige semilunar patches at transition from crown to face. Posterior margin of crown with brown streak medially. Face yellowish. Eyes blackish. Pronotum yellowish, with two irregular brown stripes below eyes and parallel to anterior margin. Basal triangles of mesonotum blackish. Fore wing beige.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,258,535]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,366,391]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Pygofer with about 4 macrosetae at cephalo-ventral angle of lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1251,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1522,1544]" captionTargetBox="[217,1386,607,1476]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1394,587,1500]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Anufrievia liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; c. apex of pygofer dorsal appendage, posterior view; d. apex of style; e. connective; f. aedeagus, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444120/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Fig. 11a</figureCitation>
); apex of dorsal appendage bifurcated, upper tooth slightly longer than the lower one (
<figureCitation box="[940,1068,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1522,1544]" captionTargetBox="[217,1386,607,1476]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1394,587,1500]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Anufrievia liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; c. apex of pygofer dorsal appendage, posterior view; d. apex of style; e. connective; f. aedeagus, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444120/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Figs 11b, c</figureCitation>
). Style with apical tooth slightly shorter than subapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[488,588,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1522,1544]" captionTargetBox="[217,1386,607,1476]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1394,587,1500]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Anufrievia liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; c. apex of pygofer dorsal appendage, posterior view; d. apex of style; e. connective; f. aedeagus, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444120/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Fig. 11d</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft straight, dorsal margin serrated medially, ventral margin expanded subapically, subapical processes slender (one missing) and long; preatrial process with base broad, apex nearly reaching gonopore; gonopore central (
<figureCitation box="[656,779,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1522,1544]" captionTargetBox="[217,1386,607,1476]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[192,1394,587,1500]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Anufrievia liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage, lateral view; c. apex of pygofer dorsal appendage, posterior view; d. apex of style; e. connective; f. aedeagus, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444120/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Figs 11f, g</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
