<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1619,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1691,1716]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Remarks:</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dworakowska" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1977" box="[669,982,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anufrievia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosa">
<emphasis box="[669,809,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">A. maculosa</emphasis>
Dworakowska
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the aedeagal shaft with the dorsal margin serrated and the ventral margin expanded subapically, and the preatrial process shorter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
